DESCRIPTION:Do finals have you feeling overwhelmed? Come destress with the University Counseling Center and West Michigan Therapy Dogs!\nWhile therapy dogs are trained to interact with a variety of people to relieve stress and provide support through comfort and affection\, they are not intended as a form of individual therapy and do not have specific treatment goals related to mental health. Please contact the University Counseling Center at (616) 331-3266 to schedule an appointment if you are concerned about your mental health.\nhttps\://gvsu.edu/events/event-526319.htm
