DESCRIPTION:Padnos College of Engineering (PCE) Project Day showcases the work of undergraduate and graduate students in Engineering and Occupational Safety and Health Management majors. Projects are a cumulation of what PCE students learned in the classroom along with soft skills and teamwork. At the conclusion of each fall and winter semester\, we invite the Greater Grand Rapids area high schools to the Shape Corp. Innovation Design Center on the PEW campus to interact with our students\, staff\, and faculty. We believe in near-peer mentorship\; this tradition highlights our students and what they can achieve in a semester\, and the inspiration their work can give to our GVSU and Grand Rapids community. \nhttps\://gvsu.edu/events/event-535662.htm
SUMMARY:Padnos College of Engineering Project Day
PRIORITY:3
