DESCRIPTION:Research shows a strong link between animal abuse and family violence. Professionals working with children\, survivors\, and families often encounter pets used as tools of control. Understanding this connection strengthens safety planning and intervention.\n Recognize warning signs\n Support families with pets in crisis\n Strengthen cross-agency collaboration\n Improve investigation and prosecution approaches\nThis training has been approved by the NASW-Michigan Chapter for 1.5 synchronous General social work CEs\: Approval Number 20260429-CA-RAEV.\nCost\: $45.00\nClick here for additional information\nhttps\://gvsu.edu/events/event-521455.htm
SUMMARY:When Animal Abuse Links to Family Violence\: Strategies for Safety
PRIORITY:3
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:94CD616A-EAD6-8D1A-72E321EE7EB2DB2B
DTSTAMP:20260225T123201
DTSTART:20260429T110000
DTEND:20260429T130000
DESCRIPTION:Join the Center for Health & Well-being throughout April for Wellness Wednesday tabling events in recognition of Sexual Assault Awareness Month. Each week focuses on practical skills\, empowerment\, and ways we can create a safer\, more respectful campus community. Stop by\, learn something new\, and grab free resources and giveaways.\nBystander intervention can prevent harm before it happens. Learn the 5 D's of intervention\, practice real-life scenarios\, and discover simple\, safe ways to step in and support others.\nClick here for additional information\nhttps\://gvsu.edu/events/event-518181.htm
SUMMARY:Wednesday Wellness - SAAM - See Something. Support Someone.
PRIORITY:3
END:VEVENT
