DESCRIPTION:We're bringing you the resources you need to start or scale your business - all in one place. It's like a job fair\, but for businesses!\nAt this open-house-styled event\, you can engage with local business support organizations and financial institutions. These organizations can assist with funding options\, market research\, business planning\, networking\, sales and marketing\, social media\, business certifications\, contracting opportunities\, and energy assessments\, and much more! Our goal is to help you (the time-limited entrepreneur) get direct access to the people you need to know to be successful.\nRegister Here.\nPlease be advised that photography and videography may take place during this event. By entering the event premises and/or participating\, you grant the Michigan Small Business Development Center (MI SBDC) permission to capture and use your image\, likeness\, and voice in any photographs\, video recordings\, or other media taken during the event.\nThese materials may be used for promotional\, educational\, or marketing purposes\, including future event advertising\, publications\, and social media\, without compensation or further notice.\nIf you prefer not to be photographed or recorded\, or do not wish your likeness to be used in promotional materials\, please contact us directly at sbdc@gvsu.edu prior to the event.\n &yuml\;Reasonable accommodations for persons with disabilities will be made if requested at least two weeks in advance.\n Funded in part through a Cooperative Agreement with the U.S. Small Business Administration. All opinions\, conclusions\, and/or recommendations expressed herein are those of the author(s) and do not necessarily reflect the views of the SBA.\nhttps\://gvsu.edu/events/event-519433.htm
SUMMARY:Small Business Resource Fair
PRIORITY:3
END:VEVENT
